 role in his film [[Blackjack (film)|Blackjack]]\n(1990). She was also the obvious choice for his film [[ÃnglagÃ¥rd\n(film)|ÃnglagÃ¥rd]] (1992) as well as its sequel \"House of Angels â the Second\nSummer\". In 1998 she played the part of Astrid in the English production \"Still\nCrazy\" which was to be followed by Colin Nutleyâs Oscar-nominated \"Under the\nSun\" - a film that also received the Special Jury Prize at the San Sebastian\nFilm Festival \"for the quality of its acting\".\n\nWinner of several awards including Best Actress at the Swedish Film Awards, the\nMontreal Film Festival and the 1995 Istanbul Film Festival for her performance\nin Nutleyâs \"The Last Dance\".\n\nIn 2007 she made her directorial debut with \"Mind the Gap\" (Se upp fÃ¶r dÃ¥rarna).\n\nBergstrÃ¶m hosted Melodifestivalen 2012 along with Gina Dirawi and Sarah\nDawn Finer.\n\nHas two children, a son and a daughter (actress Molly Nutley), with Nutley.\n","linknr":152,"url":"Helena_Bergström","recorded":1375086933,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Helena_Bergstr%C3%B6m&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Helena_Bergstr%C3%B6m&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a4/Text_docum